result.name: Bak Kut King

reviews.text: Great Singapore and Malaysia restaurant here. Service is great and helpful, reasonable price with good taste of foods. Here were many traditional dishes to choose from. I highly recommend the curry prawn and pineapple prawn fried rice. Really delicious!
Malay style Bak Kut Teh, nice aroma with a little bit sweetness. The ribs also tasty.
Laksa was too salty for me although it was very aromatic. I added water to dilute it.

So today we passed by this Malaysia restaurant and decided to give it a try. 

It's summer and it's burning hot out there. To combat the heat, I ordered the ice sour plum drink. It's perfect for this weather. 

Milo dinosaur is pretty awesome. It reminds me of my childhood memories. It's a bit too sweet of my liking now, but I enjoyed it. 

I'm honestly impressed with the althenticity of their laksa noodles. The mixed noodles gives it a distinct texture resembling the authentic Laksa Noddles. The shimp is fresh and the soup is right on. 

The Malay choconut pasted rice is refreshing. It has a hint of sweetness to it. On the side, it comes with some dressings that you can pair with the rice. Frankly, one of the dressing is too hot for me. The chicken wings are quite good too. 

The meat floss naan is quite surprising. It's a perfect snack. Never tried this before and I like it. 

Overall, if you happen to pass by this restaurant, be sure to check it out.

This restaurant used to be my favourite a year ago, but I am really disappointed on my order tonight. I ordered a vegetarian laksa and a hot barley drink. The taste of laksa was very different from before. It should be Singaporean laksa soup made of coconut milk and spices but now changed to tom yum soup. The hot barley drink has smelled like which had made for so long ago and became bad. I told the waitress politely the drink went bad. The waitress smelled the drink. I could tell she agreed with me but she’s too green to make decision. After awhile, there was another lady come to us and said the drink was made today. I told her I was living in Singapore for a long time and I could tell the drink went bad. She then stated “ I just made it and will not refund.” I didn’t want to make a scene but I am very sure she lied. It was because it takes at least 30-45mins to cook barley to expand and soften normally. They only took 10mins to serve me the drink. I am very disappointed on this restarant and will not visit once more. If you are the person love Singaporean food, I recommended you not bother to try.

result.name: 肉骨皇

reviews.text: 肉骨茶必食😋 脆皮豬手肉嫩皮脆👍
好正嘅肉骨茶😁

今個weekend我哋一早就plan好晒lunch食乜嘢， 事關為食無得醫， 聽到朋友食呢間肉骨茶話味道好正， 就專程由新界西出銅鑼灣大坑， 搵食真係唔怕遠㗎。

因為lunch, 所以唔係點左好多嘢食，連埋甜品， 我就揀咗三樣， 全部都係星馬特產。

1) 肉骨茶 (大份）
2) 怡寶芽菜雞
3) 焗特色咖椰土司磚配雪糕

肉骨茶佢除左油炸鬼同醬汁外， 仲係連埋個小火爐一齊上， 所以食嗰陣時仲係熱辣辣咁樣食嘢， 王牌真係王牌， 個肉骨茶嗰個湯 (茶）係好香濃，我哋係會追住飲囉飲完一碗又一碗🤤👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻 怡寶芽菜雞我都係第一次食，個雞點埋佢啲醬汁係可以帶出鮮味， good.

最估唔到就係個甜品，焗咖椰土司磚配雪糕， 個土司磚正牌外脆卜卜， 內鬆軟呀， 點埋個雪糕食係超正呀！

大坑美食多， 但你又知不知道在大坑有一間以正宗星馬菜閒名的餐廳？
這裏的招牌菜可說是肉骨茶， 無他， 因為他的肉骨茶非常足料， 而且有如馬來西亞地道的肉骨茶一般安放了很多藥材。
另外非常欣賞這裏的 沙嗲， 我分別點了豬牛雞沙嗲各兩串。 可能因為我個人比較愛吃牛肉， 我認為牛肉串燒做得最出色， 牛肉烤得軟身， 和沙嗲醬非常配合。
還點了 半山熟獅蚶， 未到水準完全不下 潮州打冷舖！
建議愛吃星馬菜的人要過嚟試一試。

🔍大坑浣紗街45號浣紗花園地下1號舖

「回味無窮 肉骨茶初體驗」- 肉骨皇 (大坑)

大坑真係好多好野食，本次經過肉骨皇都聞到好大陣好香濃既肉骨茶既藥材味。其實我一直都好想試下肉骨茶，所以就決定去呢間星馬餐廳試試佢。

肉骨茶（細）+白飯 （$98+$10）
店員好快就拎左個爐過黎煲熱啲肉骨茶。原諒我係第一次食肉骨茶同太肚餓既關係，未等到個煲滾已經食左個油炸鬼（後尾先知係浸湯食）。
係煲既時候已經聞到好香既藥材味，我已經流哂口水，店員會幫我地睇火，等左10-15分鐘之後就食得！
本身會覺得肉骨茶係好藥材，但點知飲落係好香又帶點甜味，啲配料同個肉都煮到好入味。無論係送飯、定係就咁飲都好好味！🤤🤤

海鮮喇沙-兩溝Mix （$98）
喇沙湯底好香濃，有啲椰香味但唔太出，唔算好辣。海鮮都好出色好足料，有青口、大蝦、小蝦、魚片。麵底揀左油麵同米粉兩溝，可以一次過試哂兩個麵底！

原味油酥餅 （$48）
油酥餅好酥脆，熱辣辣新鮮出爐，唔算好油。沾埋個咖哩汁真係一流！好食到停唔到。😆😆

呢排做緊promotion, like fb/ follow ig, 仲會送飲品添！我就揀左珍多冰，真係好抵。下次會再黎試下其他菜。

🍽8/10
